2k+1
x = \arctan u
\int \tan^{2k} dx = \int \frac{u^{2k}}{u^2+1}\,du.
\frac{u^{2k}}{u^2+1}=\frac{(-1)^k}{u^2+1}+\frac{u^{2k}-(-1)^k}{u^2+1}=\frac{(-1)^k}{u^2+1}-\sum_{j=1}^{k}(-1)^j\; u^{2k-2j},
\int \tan^{2k} dx = (-1)^k x -\sum_{j=1}^{k}\frac{(-1)^j}{2k-2j+1}(\tan x)^{2k-2j+1},
\int \tan^{2k} dx = (-1)^k x -\sum_{j=0}^{k-1}\frac{(-1)^{k+j}}{2j+1}(\tan x)^{2j+1}.
